<br>
I use Gift of Xev to summon my bag (I place the summoned pack in the top left) and place food and water in top two slots that summoned bag (since you eat from top bag first) I place bandages in next slot and fill other slots with lev. rings (leaving one slot in the bag for see invis. stave) I place rod outside of bag now to visually see I have charges left and I use weight reducing packs for everything else...Rallic pack handmade packs etc...I use bandages to fill empty spots in the summoned bag as I use up lev. rings (I dont like empty spots in my summoned pack) and I also use bandages to fill up other empty spots in other packs just in case I need to do a mass dropping of summoned focus items. <p>&lt;a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=274568&gt; Kshipper Arch Mage &lt;/a&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#333333>(12/10/02 8:28:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1695.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned bags</span><hr size=1> I have a Rallic pack, EE bag, and a normal backpack, and the rest are summoned bags via Gift of Xev.  Expensive loot goes into the non-summoned bags, normal junk goes into the summoned.  As long as you check before logging out, it really hasn't been a problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 387<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 8:57:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1695.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned bags</span><hr size=1> The way I figure it, anything that I would normally leave behind is fair game for a summoned bag. I routinely fill summoned bags with fine steel or equivelant weapons, blocks of ore, or any interesting trinkets that drop that may sell for a few plat. I lost a couple of bags of fine steel once by going LD before I sold them, but never anything more valuable. Just stay in the habit of NEVER putting anything of true value in one, even for a moment. Anything that manages to make it back to the vender or banker I consider free loot that would have been left behind normally.<br>
<br>
Combining the no rent bags in tandem with a few real weight reduction bags keeps me pretty far from encumbered, unless I'm carrying a lot of plat loot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=canelin@themagicianstower>Canelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 2:37:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1695.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned bags</span><hr size=1> I have :<br>
